One of the most lovely elements of the house tour decorations were the incredibly beautiful flower arrangements by @lemondahliaflowers!  Star of the show was the magnificent arrangement in the entry hall with vibrant amaryllis, spider lilies, thistle, berries, juniper and various evergreens laden with pine cones…  Perfect in the giant vintage Chinese blue and white planter from @antiqueartisan.
#hilderbrandinteriors #hilderbrandchristmas #newcanaanholidayhousetour  #classicchristmas #classicinterior #antiquehouse

Anything cozier than a wood paneled study decorated for the holidays?  We kept the decorations low key, but they are rich with detail — we used a base of fir garland, laced with white pine and cuttings from a gorgeous umbrella pine tree from client’s property… in the corners are glitter tipped pine cones, various quail and pheasant feathers, tiny twigs, feathered birds and pine cones… it all feels right at home.
#hilderbrandinteriors #hilderbrandchristmas #classicinterior #classicchristmas #newcanaanholidayhousetour #woodpaneledstudy

Quick break from the house tour… Just hit the market:  Sweet 3BR A-frame… ZOOM in for all of the details, esp Santa’s little 🔥 in the last pic.
🎅🏻 Want this house? Raffle 🎟 @greenwichhistory (see below)
PRO TIP:  ask your local bakery for gingerbread house frosting.  It hardens like cement.  I made my own last year and it was a disaster.  I’m sure there are excellent recipes online too… more tips below.
🎅🏻Raffle of this gingerbread house (and two more!) to benefit the @greenwichhistory at the Winter Market with @thelocalvault!  Come to The Local Vault design shop and dozens of other local vendors and artisans… 
🎅🏻Market today 9:30-5, Sat 9:30-4 at Christ Church on East Putnam in Greenwich.
🎅🏻 Thank you to Black Forest Pastry Shop in Greenwich for the house and frosting - the best!🙌
🎅🏻 “Logs” here are Tootsie Rolls, cut in half lengthwise (so they’re flat on the back - lighter & easier to apply)
🎅🏻 Holly leaves are @wiltoncakes — they have all things sprinkles and cake/cookie decorating!
🎅🏻 miniature Heath bars are the foundation all around (flat, easy, take up some room
🎅🏻 Nonpareils (roof shingles) are from @nutsdotcom.  Start from the bottom and work your way up so they overlap.  I used @redvinescandy the bottom edge of the roof and let that icing set up, then applied the shingles, so they wouldn’t slide down.
🎅🏻 Candy canes are used as brackets for structural support - before the icing dries, they provide strict support for big pretzels 
#gingerbreadhouse #classicchristmas #hilderbrandchristmas #wiltoncakes #lindtlove #tootsieroll 
@wiltoncakes @tootsieroll @hersheys @utzsnacks @lindt_usa @redvinescandy

Back to the holiday house tour, and our favorite kitchen, but now with gingerbread houses!  My client made gorgeous gingerbread houses for her kitchen on the tour… I think the frosted mini-wheats are genius.  I’m becoming slightly obsessed with gingerbread houses.😛🎅🏻 I’ll post a video of last year’s debacle🤦🏻‍♀️🙃 and more pics of this in STORIES.
This gorgeous 📷 @janebeilesphoto. 
#hilderbrandchristmas #hilderbrandinteriors 
#LHNewCanaan1903 #classicinterior #whitekitchen

Between the kitchen and the dining room, with view through to the living room, we completed a gorgeous butler’s pantry and bar just days before the house tour (had been plain Sheetrock just months before)… the goal was to make it feel like it had always been there. Aesthetically, tall cabinets mimic those in the kitchen for a sense of place; mirror panels add life; rich grey transitions nicely from white kitchen to darker dining room.  Practically, built-ins all around provide ample storage; and ice maker, beverage fridge and dishwasher are perfectly convenient.  Marble countertops left and right are ideal for making/serving drinks or staging for dinner or parties inside and out (door to patio reflected in mirror…).
#hilderbrandinteriors #hilderbrandchristmas #butlerspantry #perfectbar #classicinterior #dreampantry #LHNewCanaan1903

Off of yesterday’s butler’s pantry is the jewel box powder room, also finished just in time for the tour… antique oak cabinet picks up on the oak millwork throughout the house, panoramic wallpaper echos client’s love for the West. As always, the small details make a difference — intricate parquetry mirror, woven paper shades, antique leather and brass stag-mounted racks as towel hooks.
#hilderbrandinteriors #classicinterior #powderroom #antiquehouse #lhnewcanaan1903

Magnificent dining room decked for the holidays for the holiday house tour… we embraced the rich oak millwork and formality with velvet wallpaper.  Client had lovely antiques, and we took the formal edge off with mountain grass on the floor and a printed linen tablecloth.  The intense red and pink flowers by @lemondahliaflowers were total perfection.
Most pics 📷 @janebeilesphoto 
#hilderbrandinteriors #hilderbrandchristmas #holidayhousetour #LHNewCanaan1903  #formaldiningroom #antiquehouse #christmasinconnecticut

Last shot of the singularly beautiful tree from my client’s home on the New Canaan holiday house tour — the perfect Frazier fir, wrapped with 7000 lights and glistening with glass, glittered and beaded ornaments…
📷 @bygeorgiagrace - one of the best pics from the tour!✨
🎅🏻 Full cover-story feature in @bedfordnewcanaanmag ✨
🎅🏻 Scroll back through my feed from the last week to walk back through the house…
🎅🏻 @brittanytess how did you do alllll of those lights? 
🎅🏻 @lemondahliaflowers created the most beautiful flower arrangements all around!
🎅🏻So many volunteers helped me deck each mantel, wrap each column and banister… 
🎅🏻 @poundridgenursery donated miles of thick fir, pine and cedar garland. 
🎅🏻 Tree - GREGG’S NURSERY @ Weed&Duryea New Canaan 
#hilderbrandchristmas #LHNewCanaan1903 #classicinterior #classicchristmas #perfectchristmas #christmastree #newcanaanholidayhousetour

The rare mid-decoration picture… We are a little behind this year but will finish this tree today — appx 3000 lights this time (don’t @ me about the dark spots). Only 10 tubs of ornaments to go! 🙃
🎅🏻My favorite unexpected thing this season is this snuggly fleece footie suit from @lazyoneinc - purchased (sort of) as a joke, but now it a practical favorite in our chilly old house…
#hilderbrandchristmas #christmastree #footiepajamas

Oh Christmas tree… best part of it is all of the ornaments that remind us of places we’ve been, or things or people we love… 
I’m out of gas on this one - really could have used my dad.  I’m sure he was laughing at me as I yelled at the boys to not put heavy ornaments on the ends, to tuck in the lights, not cluster all of the red balls in one spot and to hide the crap ornaments on the back (they add color but you can’t really see them…). Alas… Merry Christmas and happy holidays! 
#hilderbrandchristmas

Up late, straightening up after napping by the fire most of the day… tree always wompy by now.  Time to turn off the lights and go up.  Good night quiet house.  In my mind, hearing my father ask “how many more days?” Merry Christmas.😌✨
Outdoor fireplace festive through the winter…

Perfect light this morning.
New Day.  New Year!
Our mantras for 2023:
👉Progress every day (thanks @christopherspitzmiller)
👉Nothing good happens while we wait.
👉Comparison is the thief of joy.
…and one from SM 🤗 “It’s showtime!”

SWIPE for BEFORE… So many dramatic before and afters in this house, which was taken down to the studs and subfloor throughout. 
…but this dining room…
Goodbye to the odd fireplace which pinched the room.  We lost the choppy coffered ceiling and replaced the busy tall paneling with simpler panel mounding.  Simple mountain grass on the floor, early 19th century wide mahogany dining table always beautiful, 18th century Japanese screen, pair of Biedermeier feminine tables surmounted by funky mixed metal 1970s mirrors… more on that ceiling in Stories.
Architect:  @sutroarchitects 
Builder:  @thetobonigroup 
📷 @johnmerkl 
#hilderbrandinteriors #classicinterior #diningroomdesign #antiques #sanfranciscodesign #pacificheights

Been showing beautiful formal rooms in our recent San Francisco project, but one of my favorite rooms is the primary bath… each piece of this custom @waterworks floor mosaic was carefully placed (and each wall piece in the shower). Drawers are fitted with outlets, so hairdryer etc are easy to use then neatly stowed away.  Mirrors are custom finished corner frames and are heated from behind to prevent fogging… no detail overlooked.

Christmas tree such a walk down memory lane… laden with ornaments collected near and far over the years.  Still another couple of boxes to go… some of my favorites: a little felt frog (from a song my dad used to sing when we were little “Froggy Went a Courtin’”), a big sassy Cactus from Neiman’s day-after Christmas sale 25 years ago in Dallas…, two moustached chili peppers 🌶 (for my brother, who consumed dozens of stuffed jalapeños over Christmas week a few years ago), lobsters for the Cape and Nantucket, Sasquatch from our 109mph drive across Nebraska, the Golden Gate Bridge, a giant sequoia, felt Rocky Balboa, Mt Vernon, Monticello, Bergdorf’s chic shopper and dapper doorman (a la Jennifer Quinn from @elinhilderbrand’s Winter Street novels), so many more…
